</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF51FF1BA7ADFBF6FC78D8F0" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF51FF1BA7ADFBF6FEF0D832" blockId="200.[189,310,1049,1075]" box="[189,310,1049,1075]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF51FF1BA7ADFBF6FEF0D832" bold="true" box="[189,310,1049,1075]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA7ADFBF6FEF0D832" bold="true" box="[189,310,1049,1075]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF51FF1BA7ADFBA7FC78D8F0" blockId="200.[189,1399,1096,1265]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
Based on the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF51FF1BA576FBA7FCA1D863" author="Rahmadi C. &amp; Kojima J." box="[614,871,1096,1123]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rahmadi" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Arachnology" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" pagination="475 - 484" part="38" refId="ref152642" refString="Rahmadi C. &amp; Kojima J. - i. 2010. Whip spiders of the genus Sarax in the Papuan region, with description of two new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Journal of Arachnology 38: 475 - 484. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / Ha 09 - 95.1" title="Whip spiders of the genus Sarax in the Papuan region, with description of two new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">
Rahmadi 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA5CDFBA6FCD3D863" box="[733,789,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
), this species may be separated from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF51FF1BA62CFB83FE46D887" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[316,384,1132,1158]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA62CFB83FE46D887" box="[316,384,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Sarax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Southeast Asia and Oceania by the following combination of characters: relatively small size (adult body length 
<quantity id="C0120F86FF51FF1BA508FB60FD6CD8AB" box="[536,682,1167,1194]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.85" metricValueMax="9.8" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" unit="mm" value="7.85" valueMax="9.8" valueMin="5.9">5.9–9.8 mm</quantity>
); sexual dimorphism absent; pedipalp tarsus with two spines, proximal spine about half as long as distal spine; leg IV tibia with 19 trichobothria, 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA39FFB5CFB60D8CC" box="[1167,1190,1203,1229]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">bt</emphasis>
situated medially on fourth basitibial article, and 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA53DFB39FD8FD8F1" box="[557,585,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">bc</emphasis>
situated closer to 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA40EFB39FCF3D8F1" box="[798,821,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">bf</emphasis>
than to 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA484FB39FC70D8F1" box="[916,950,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">sbf</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF51FF1BA7ADFAF7FE00D984" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF51FF1BA7ADFAF7FE82D933" blockId="200.[189,324,1304,1330]" box="[189,324,1304,1330]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF51FF1BA7ADFAF7FE82D933" bold="true" box="[189,324,1304,1330]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA7ADFAF7FE82D933" bold="true" box="[189,324,1304,1330]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF51FF1BA7ADFAA8FE00D984" blockId="200.[189,1399,1351,1413]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
Adjective derived from the Sangkulirang Karst formation in 
<collectingCountry id="7FFDE2F3FF51FF1BA4A9FAA8FBE8D960" box="[953,1070,1351,1377]" name="Indonesia" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, where the species occurs (
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF51FF1BA7D5FA84FE7CD984" author="Rahmadi C. &amp; Kojima J." box="[197,442,1387,1413]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rahmadi" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Arachnology" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" pagination="475 - 484" part="38" refId="ref152642" refString="Rahmadi C. &amp; Kojima J. - i. 2010. Whip spiders of the genus Sarax in the Papuan region, with description of two new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Journal of Arachnology 38: 475 - 484. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / Ha 09 - 95.1" title="Whip spiders of the genus Sarax in the Papuan region, with description of two new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">
Rahmadi 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF51FF1BA628FA83FEB5D984" box="[312,371,1387,1413]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
